Types of Repositories
1). Bare Repositories(central)
  a). Store & Share only
  b). All central repositories are bare repositories

2). Non-Bare Repositories(Local)
  a). Where you can modify the files
  b). All local/user repositories.

why only Git  ?

- Speed
   . snapshots concept
-parellal branching
   . multiple branches at a time unlike other SCM tools
-fully distributed

